WEBVTT

00:03.703 --> 00:05.572
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

00:05.605 --> 00:09.142
WHOO!

00:09.175 --> 00:11.177
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

00:12.579 --> 00:16.583
Dani:<i>WHEN IT'S WORKING,</i>
<i>A TEAM FUNCTIONS AS A UNIT --</i>

00:16.616 --> 00:21.087
<i>EVERYONE'S FOCUSED ON THE GOAL,</i>
<i>IN SYNC...</i>

00:21.121 --> 00:22.188
Man: HUT!

00:23.189 --> 00:25.091
<i>...TRUSTING</i>
<i>EACH OTHER'S INSTINCTS.</i>

00:25.125 --> 00:27.260
[ LAUGHS ]
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

00:27.293 --> 00:30.196
Man: OKAY, LADIES OF THE HAWKS,
THIS IS FOR THE MAGAZINE COVER.

00:30.230 --> 00:32.165
SMILES, PLEASE. BEAUTIFUL!

00:32.198 --> 00:33.600
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
EXCELLENT!

00:33.633 --> 00:37.237
<i>BUT WHEN A TEAM FALLS APART,</i>
<i>NO ONE'S GOT YOUR BACK.</i>

00:37.270 --> 00:39.172
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]
<i>OR EVEN WORSE,</i>

00:39.205 --> 00:41.174
<i>THEY'RE</i>ON<i>YOUR BACK.</i>

00:41.207 --> 00:44.244
<i>AND YOU START TO WONDER --</i>
<i>ARE YOU EVEN ON A TEAM,</i>

00:44.277 --> 00:46.613
<i>OR ARE YOU PLAYING</i>
<i>ALL BY YOURSELF?</i>

00:46.646 --> 00:48.348
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES ]

00:48.381 --> 00:51.251
THIS IS GREAT.

00:51.284 --> 00:52.686
RAY JAY WROTE THIS?

00:52.719 --> 00:54.320
KEEP READING.

00:54.354 --> 00:56.356
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THE KIDS IN THE STORY

00:56.389 --> 00:57.457
LIVE WITH THEIR DAD.

00:57.490 --> 00:59.192
...AND READING.

00:59.225 --> 01:00.326
AND THE MOTHER IS...

01:00.360 --> 01:01.594
DEAD!

01:01.628 --> 01:04.297
MARGO, SHE'S DEAD.

01:04.330 --> 01:06.399
THIS IS FICTION.
DON'T GET YOUR PANTIES IN A WAD.

01:06.433 --> 01:08.668
SEE, THE FATHER
IS THE HERO, YEAH?

01:08.702 --> 01:10.904
THE MOTHER ABANDONS
THE FAMILY,

01:10.937 --> 01:13.406
AND THEN SHE GETS
A BRAIN TUMOR!

01:13.440 --> 01:16.910
THE PSYCHOLOGICAL IMPLICATIONS
ARE PRETTY OBVIOUS HERE.

01:16.943 --> 01:19.212
RAY JAY FEELS ABANDONED
BY ME

01:19.245 --> 01:21.715
BECAUSE OF MY NEW JOB
WITH THE HAWKS.

01:21.748 --> 01:25.218
I DON'T WORK AT ALL,
AND MY KIDS STILL<i>HATE</i>ME.

01:25.251 --> 01:27.153
DON'T BE SO HARD
ON YOURSELF.

01:27.187 --> 01:28.688
LAST YEAR,
YOU BAKED EVERY BROWNIE...

01:28.722 --> 01:31.491
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THAT MY SON
HAD ANY WRITING TALENT.

01:31.524 --> 01:34.461
AND HE JUST GOT NAMED CO-CAPTAIN
OF THE FOOTBALL TEAM,

01:34.494 --> 01:36.229
AND I HAVEN'T EVEN HOSTED

01:36.262 --> 01:39.466
ANY OF THOSE CRAZY
TEAM-DINNER THINGS.

01:39.499 --> 01:42.202
THAT'S A LOT OF WORK
FOR A WORKING MOM.

01:43.403 --> 01:45.238
EXCEPT...

01:45.271 --> 01:47.173
IF I HAD SOME HELP

01:47.207 --> 01:50.944
FROM ANOTHER TEAM MOM
EXTRAORDINAIRE.

01:50.977 --> 01:53.380
I ONLY UNDERSTAND FRENCH
WHEN YOU'RE OFFERING ME WINE.

01:53.413 --> 01:54.714
WINE, IT IS!

01:54.748 --> 01:57.684
YAY! NO, MARGO.
WE CAN DO THIS. OKAY?

01:57.717 --> 02:02.188
RAY JAY IS NOT
GONNA KILL ME OFF...

02:02.222 --> 02:04.357
WITHOUT A FIGHT.

02:04.391 --> 02:05.525
WHAT A MESS.

02:05.558 --> 02:07.627
I THOUGHT SHANNON AND LEANNE
WERE FRIENDS.

02:07.660 --> 02:10.363
AND THESE ARE
TEAM WIVES?

02:10.397 --> 02:13.600
WAGS.
WIVES AND GIRLFRIENDS.

02:13.633 --> 02:16.436
OKAY.
WHAT EXACTLY HAPPENED?

02:16.469 --> 02:17.771
A MAGAZINE SHOOT.

02:17.804 --> 02:18.772
[ BEEP ]

02:18.805 --> 02:20.774
"STARS BEHIND THE STARS."

02:20.807 --> 02:23.710
OUR ILLUSTRIOUS PUBLICIST
LAURA RADCLIFFE'S IDEA.

02:23.743 --> 02:24.611
THE HITTING
AND THE SHOVING --

02:24.644 --> 02:26.312
THEY CAME UP WITH THAT
ALL ON THEIR OWN.

02:27.313 --> 02:28.615
UNHAPPY WIVES MAKE
UNHAPPY PLAYERS, DR. DANI.

02:28.648 --> 02:30.383
AND UNHAPPY PLAYERS
DON'T WIN GAMES.

02:30.417 --> 02:32.352
WE ALREADY HAD TWO LINEMEN
GO AT EACH OTHER

02:32.385 --> 02:33.520
IN THE LOCKER ROOM TODAY.

02:33.553 --> 02:35.522
SO YOU WANT ME TO GO TALK
TO THE LINEMEN?

02:35.555 --> 02:37.724
NO. WE WANT YOU
TO TALK TO<i>THEM.</i>

02:39.426 --> 02:42.762
DR. DANI, THE WAGS ARE WIGGIN'.
MAKE 'EM STOP.

02:45.732 --> 02:48.601
OKAY.
IN THE LEFT CORNER,

02:48.635 --> 02:51.604
WE HAVE SHANNON PRITCHETT,
FORMER MISS OHIO,

02:51.638 --> 02:54.741
WIFE OF OUR FREE SAFETY,
RYAN PRITCHETT, ALL-STAR.

02:54.774 --> 02:56.009
SHANNON TAKES CARE OF
THE HAWKS CHARITY DRIVE

02:56.042 --> 02:57.477
AND ALMOST EVERYTHING ELSE.

02:57.510 --> 02:59.813
IN THE RIGHT CORNER,
LEANNE FLEMING.

02:59.846 --> 03:02.382
HUSBAND'S
A ROOKIE LINEBACKER.

03:02.415 --> 03:03.650
DO WE HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THEY WERE FIGHTING ABOUT?

03:03.683 --> 03:04.784
NO ONE'S TALKING.

03:04.818 --> 03:06.586
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

03:06.619 --> 03:08.221
I HAVE TO TAKE CARE
OF SOMETHING.

03:09.756 --> 03:12.292
GOOD LUCK IN THERE.

03:12.325 --> 03:13.393
[ SCOFFS ]

03:22.569 --> 03:24.471
IT WAS
A MISUNDERSTANDING.

03:24.504 --> 03:27.741
UH, WHAT WAS
THE MISUNDERSTANDING ABOUT?

03:27.774 --> 03:29.409
WE'RE A CLOSE-KNIT GROUP.

03:29.442 --> 03:31.678
WE'RE BOUND TO GET
ON EACH OTHER'S NERVES.

03:31.711 --> 03:33.813
WE APOLOGIZE
FOR ANY EMBARRASSMENT

03:33.847 --> 03:35.415
WE MAY HAVE CAUSED.

03:35.448 --> 03:39.486
DISCORD AMONGST THE WIVES
IS NOT GOOD FOR ANYBODY.

03:39.519 --> 03:42.756
YOU'RE ALL A PART
OF THE TEAM.

03:42.789 --> 03:44.457
LOOK -- WHAT WOULD THE TEAM
LIKE FROM US

03:44.491 --> 03:45.525
OTHER THAN AN APOLOGY?

03:46.493 --> 03:48.395
TO TRY AND WORK OUT THE PROBLEMS
BETWEEN YOU.

03:48.428 --> 03:50.764
I DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM,
DR. SANTINO.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.400
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:54.734 --> 03:56.870
OKAY, IN THAT CASE,
YOU DON'T MIND

03:56.903 --> 03:58.838
IF I MOVE ON WITH MY LIFE,
RIGHT?

04:01.675 --> 04:03.376
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

04:03.410 --> 04:07.313
AT THE PHOTO SHOOT,
LEANNE LOST A BRACELET,

04:07.347 --> 04:08.648
AN EXPENSIVE BRACELET.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.617
SHE BELIEVES
ONE OF US STOLE IT.

04:10.650 --> 04:12.852
SO THAT'S WHAT LED
TO THE ALTERCATION.

04:12.886 --> 04:16.356
HER ACCUSATIONS
WERE INFLAMMATORY, AND...

04:16.389 --> 04:18.792
LOOK -- UNFORTUNATELY,
THINGS KIND OF GOT OUT OF HAND.

04:18.825 --> 04:20.760
DR. SANTINO,

04:20.794 --> 04:23.096
RYAN AND I HAVE DEVOTED
OUR LIVES TO THE HAWKS

04:23.129 --> 04:24.564
FOR THE PAST EIGHT YEARS.

04:24.597 --> 04:26.633
THE IMAGE OF THE TEAM WIVES
IS SOMETHING THAT

04:26.666 --> 04:28.435
I FEEL PROTECTIVE OF...

04:28.468 --> 04:29.803
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
...SOMETHING
I-I WOULD NEVER --

04:29.836 --> 04:31.671
[ SIGHS ]
THIS IS MY NANNY.

04:31.705 --> 04:33.406
I...I HAVE TO
TAKE THIS.

04:33.440 --> 04:34.541
OH.

04:34.574 --> 04:36.409
MORNING. BLANCA?

04:36.443 --> 04:38.845
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

04:45.785 --> 04:47.687
Nico:
WHAT'S HE ON, JULIETTE?

04:47.721 --> 04:51.424
HE'S FINE. I HAD MORE TO DRINK
LAST NIGHT THAN HE DID.

04:51.458 --> 04:52.859
AND YOU'RE PROUD OF THAT?

04:56.863 --> 05:00.800
[ SIGHS ]

05:05.772 --> 05:07.974
HE'LL SLEEP IT OFF.

05:08.008 --> 05:10.710
YOU 911'ed ME
TO WAKE UP SLEEPING BEAUTY?

05:10.744 --> 05:13.613
SOMETHING WAS STOLEN
FROM ME, NICO.

05:13.646 --> 05:16.883
OH, SORRY.
CALL THE COPS.

05:16.916 --> 05:20.854
OH! LOOK -- HE -- KURT AND I
WERE SCREWING AROUND,

05:20.887 --> 05:23.890
AND WE DECIDED
TO RECORD IT.

05:23.923 --> 05:24.858
JUST -- JUST TO SEE
WHAT IT WOULD LOOK LIKE.

05:25.625 --> 05:26.760
AND SOMEHOW
THE TAPE GOT STOLEN.

05:26.793 --> 05:27.761
AND NOW THEY WANT MONEY...

05:27.794 --> 05:29.996
TO GET THE TAPE BACK.

05:30.030 --> 05:32.599
LOOK -- THEY KNOW
MY FAMILY HAS MONEY

05:32.632 --> 05:35.535
AND THAT KURT'S AN
ALL-AMERICAN FORWARD AT A.T.U.

05:35.568 --> 05:37.437
JULIETTE, I --
PLEASE,
I KNOW I SCREWED UP.

05:37.470 --> 05:41.708
I DRINK TOO MUCH,
AND I PARTY TOO HARD, AND...

05:41.741 --> 05:43.943
JUST YOU'VE ALWAYS
TAKEN CARE OF ME.

05:43.977 --> 05:46.479
I HAVE STRICT INSTRUCTIONS
FROM YOUR FATHER --

05:46.513 --> 05:47.914
NOT TO ANSWER YOUR CALLS,
NOT TO STEP IN AGAIN.

05:47.947 --> 05:49.549
YOU KNOW THAT.

05:49.582 --> 05:50.817
WELL,
I'M SURE MARSHALL PITTMAN,

05:50.850 --> 05:52.018
OWNER OF
THE NEW YORK HAWKS,

05:52.052 --> 05:53.953
DOESN'T WANT YOU TO LET
HIS ONLY DAUGHTER

05:53.987 --> 05:55.622
HAVE A SEX TAPE
FLOAT AROUND THE INTERNET.

06:00.560 --> 06:03.763
Irv:<i>THIS IS IRV SUPERFON</i>
<i>HERE ON WNYJ.</i>

06:03.797 --> 06:06.199
<i>WE HAVE SCOTT FROM BROOKLYN</i>
<i>ON THE LINE.</i>

06:06.232 --> 06:08.702
<i>SCOTT, WHAT DO YOU GOT TO SAY</i>
<i>TO TERRENCE KING?</i>

06:08.735 --> 06:10.804
Scott:<i>WHAT'S UP, T.K.?</i>
<i>YOU SUCK, MAN.</i>

06:10.837 --> 06:12.772
T.K.:
<i>HEY, SCOTT. SUCK THIS.</i>

06:12.806 --> 06:14.874
<i>DOUCHE BAG. GET A JOB.</i>

06:14.908 --> 06:18.745
Irv:<i>T.K., YOU GOT YOUR GAME</i>
<i>BACK EARLIER THIS SEASON,</i>

06:18.778 --> 06:20.447
<i>NO QUESTION,</i>
<i>BUT SOME OF THE FANS</i>

06:21.681 --> 06:22.015
<i>SAY SHANE GIVENS IS GIVING YOU</i>
<i>A RUN FOR YOUR MONEY.</i>

06:23.116 --> 06:25.518
T.K.:<i>WELL, SHANE'S NICKNAME</i>
<i>IS "LITTLE T.K."</i>

06:25.552 --> 06:27.520
<i>AND THAT'S ONLY 'CAUSE</i>
<i>I CALLED HIM "LITTLE TEA CAKE."</i>

06:27.554 --> 06:28.655
<i>ALL RIGHT?</i>
<i>AND YOU CAN TELL SCOTT</i>

06:28.688 --> 06:31.524
<i>AND THE REST OF THOSE</i>
<i>UNEMPLOYED, WANNABE LOSERS</i>

06:31.558 --> 06:32.926
<i>TO MOVE THEIR ASSES</i>
<i>TO NEW JERSEY.</i>

06:32.959 --> 06:35.028
Irv:<i>YOU CALLING HAWKS FANS</i>
<i>UNEMPLOYED LOSERS?</i>

06:35.061 --> 06:37.530
T.K.:<i>THEY CAN EITHER</i>
<i>GET ON THE T.K. TRAIN</i>

06:37.564 --> 06:41.067
<i>OR GET ON THE SHANE TRAIN</i>
<i>AND KISS MY BLACK ASS!</i>

06:41.101 --> 06:42.769
OH, OKAY.

06:42.802 --> 06:44.537
TERRENCE...

06:44.571 --> 06:47.007
I BOOK YOU ON "IRV SUPERFON'S
TALK IN THE MORNING" --

06:47.040 --> 06:49.709
NUMBER-ONE SPORTS TALK SHOW,
COVETED SPOT.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.846
AND YOU DECIDE TO INSULT
THE FANS OF NEW YORK CITY,

06:52.879 --> 06:54.848
AS WELL
AS A FELLOW TEAMMATE?

06:54.881 --> 06:56.983
I JUST, I --
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

06:57.017 --> 06:59.252
FIRST OF ALL,
THE FANS STARTED IT.

06:59.285 --> 07:00.887
ALL RIGHT?

07:00.920 --> 07:03.056
THEY DO A LIST OF THE
TOP 50 MOST BELOVED ATHLETES,

07:03.089 --> 07:05.925
AND T.K. IS NUMBER 47.

07:05.959 --> 07:09.529
SHANE GIVENS -- 25.

07:09.562 --> 07:11.064
YOU MAY EXPLAIN.

07:11.097 --> 07:14.934
YOU'RE MISSING THE POINT.
YOU MADE THE LIST.

07:14.968 --> 07:17.570
T., LISTEN.

07:17.604 --> 07:20.573
A MONTH AGO,
YOU WERE A LIABILITY.

07:20.607 --> 07:22.976
AND THEN LAURA GOT YOU
SPORT-E BOOST,

07:23.009 --> 07:25.011
A SHOE DEAL,
DOING NATIONAL TALK SHOWS.

07:25.045 --> 07:27.981
BETWEEN THE WORK YOU'RE DOING
WITH LAURA AND DANI,

07:28.014 --> 07:29.849
YOU'RE FINALLY
BACK ON TRACK, BRO.

07:29.883 --> 07:31.985
"BACK ON TRACK"?

07:32.018 --> 07:33.753
"BACK ON TRACK,"
HE SAYS.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.755
[ LAUGHS ]
I'M 47 OUT OF 50.

07:35.789 --> 07:37.991
"BACK ON TRACK."
THAT'S NOT BACK ON TRACK.

07:38.024 --> 07:39.592
THAT'S A BIG-ASS DERAILMENT,
DAWG,

07:39.626 --> 07:42.729
ESPECIALLY WHEN SHANE GIVENS
IS NUMBER 25.

07:42.762 --> 07:44.497
AND IT IS<i>YOUR</i>JOB TO FIX IT.

07:46.566 --> 07:47.934
SO FIX IT.

07:51.037 --> 07:55.642
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

08:05.251 --> 08:07.120
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

08:17.731 --> 08:20.233
REALLY?
IT'S 11:30 AT NIGHT.

08:20.266 --> 08:22.168
WE HAVE A SITUATION.

08:22.202 --> 08:24.804
HOW COME NONE OF YOUR SITUATIONS
HAPPEN AT A NORMAL TIME?

08:24.838 --> 08:27.707
BECAUSE JAIL TIME
BECAUSE JAIL TIME
<i>AN</i>TIME.

08:27.741 --> 08:29.309
JAIL TIME?

08:30.910 --> 08:33.780
SHANNON?
WHAT HAPPENED?

08:36.383 --> 08:39.853
I WAS ARRESTED...

08:39.886 --> 08:41.755
FOR SHOPLIFTING.

08:42.956 --> 08:44.324
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

08:46.626 --> 08:50.230
I-I-I HAVE THINGS
AT MY HOME --

08:50.263 --> 08:52.766
THINGS THAT I DIDN'T BUY.

08:52.799 --> 08:55.235
THINGS YOU'VE STOLEN.

08:55.268 --> 08:58.805
AND LEANNE'S BRACELET?

08:58.838 --> 09:01.675
[ SIGHS ]

09:01.708 --> 09:03.343
GOD, I BARELY REMEMBER
TAKING IT.

09:03.376 --> 09:05.245
I FEEL SUCH SHAME.

09:05.278 --> 09:07.847
I UNDERSTAND.

09:07.881 --> 09:10.984
I-I'VE NEVER DONE
ANYTHING LIKE THIS BEFORE.

09:11.017 --> 09:14.254
SHOPLIFTING IS OFTEN TRIGGERED
BY A KIND OF NEED

09:14.287 --> 09:18.391
OR LOSS OR DEPRESSION.

09:18.425 --> 09:20.894
WELL, I-I COME
FROM A TOUGH HOME.

09:20.927 --> 09:23.997
I ROSE ABOVE IT,
I GOT MARRIED, HAD KIDS.

09:24.030 --> 09:26.766
WE HAVE A BEAUTIFUL LIFE
TOGETHER, DR. SANTINO.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.268
WHY WOULD
I SCREW ALL THAT UP?

09:33.973 --> 09:37.644
HEY, KID.
GET IN THE CAR.

09:37.677 --> 09:38.912
YOU THE GUY
FROM THE PHONE?

09:38.945 --> 09:40.380
YEAH. I AM.

09:45.251 --> 09:46.853
YOU GOT THE MONEY,
RIGHT?

09:46.886 --> 09:49.389
YOU GOT
WHAT I ASKED FOR?

10:00.033 --> 10:02.802
WAIT. THIS IS LIKE
LESS THAN 200 BUCKS.

10:02.836 --> 10:04.337
OVER THE PHONE,
YOU SAID IT WOULD BE --
[ DOORS LOCK ]

10:04.371 --> 10:05.972
WHAT THE HELL, DUDE?

10:08.041 --> 10:10.310
ARE THERE COPIES,
CHARLES?

10:10.343 --> 10:11.745
HOW DO YOU KNOW MY NAME?

10:11.778 --> 10:13.947
COPIES.
ARE...THERE...COPIES?

10:13.980 --> 10:16.950
IF ANYTHING ABOUT THIS GIRL
GETS IN THE PUBLIC EYE

10:16.983 --> 10:19.085
IN ANY WAY, I'M GONNA BE
A VERY PISSED OFF GUY.

10:19.119 --> 10:20.353
"THIS GIRL"?

10:20.387 --> 10:22.055
THE GIRL ON THE DISC,
CHARLES.

10:22.088 --> 10:23.857
THERE IS NO GIRL
ON THE DISC.

10:23.890 --> 10:25.859
YOU THINK
I'M PLAYING GAMES?

10:25.892 --> 10:27.794
NO, I'M TELLING YOU --
IT'S A DRUG BUY.

10:27.827 --> 10:29.996
OKAY, SOME BIG
COLLEGE BASKETBALL STAR.

10:30.030 --> 10:32.032
BUT THERE IS NO GIRL
ON THE DISC, I SWEAR.

10:37.437 --> 10:39.372
MOM, WE'RE OUT
OF PEPPERONI.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.741
THERE'S SOME MORE ON THE TABLE
OVER THERE.

10:43.076 --> 10:44.844
CHAPTER 2.

10:44.878 --> 10:46.446
THE BRAIN TUMOR,
IT IS OPERABLE,

10:46.479 --> 10:48.415
AND THE KIDS ABANDON
THEIR FATHER

10:48.448 --> 10:49.816
ON A RAT-INFESTED
ISLAND.

10:49.849 --> 10:50.950
NICE!

10:50.984 --> 10:52.919
HERE IS TO WORKING MOMS
SUCCEEDING.

10:52.952 --> 10:54.754
RIGHT?

10:54.788 --> 10:56.456
WORK DON'T GOT TO TRAMPLE
ON THE HOME LIFE.

10:56.489 --> 10:57.457
IT CAN BE DONE.

10:57.490 --> 10:58.925
THAT IS RIGHT.

10:58.958 --> 10:59.926
[ LAUGHS ]

10:59.959 --> 11:00.994
T.K.: HIDEY-HO!

11:01.027 --> 11:02.762
[ CHEERING ]

11:04.431 --> 11:07.934
HEY, WHICH ONE OF Y'ALL WANT TO
PLAY FOR THE NEW YORK HAWKS?

11:07.967 --> 11:09.903
YO, FOOL, WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU WERE HAVING A PARTY?

11:09.936 --> 11:12.038
Dani: TERRENCE.

11:12.072 --> 11:14.140
MOM,
HE JUST GOT HERE.

11:14.174 --> 11:18.878
UM, T.K., CAN I HAVE A WORD
WITH YOU OUTSIDE?

11:18.912 --> 11:20.113
[ ALL TALKING ]

11:21.314 --> 11:24.351
OOH.
DIRTY SIDE EYES.

11:24.384 --> 11:26.820
HOLD THAT, PIMPIN'.

11:26.853 --> 11:27.587
I'M GONNA HOLLER AT YOU.
ALL RIGHT.

11:29.823 --> 11:32.359
I'M COMING BACK FOR THAT,
THOUGH.

11:37.364 --> 11:39.532
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

11:39.566 --> 11:41.134
THE IRV SUPERFON FIASCO.

11:41.167 --> 11:42.902
IRV<i>WHO?</i>

11:42.936 --> 11:44.771
DO YOUR RESEARCH, DOC.
IT'S A SPORTS-RADIO TALK SHOW.

11:44.804 --> 11:45.939
DUDE SET ME UP,

11:47.007 --> 11:47.941
AND NOW ALL THE PAPERS
ARE TALKING MESS ABOUT ME.

11:49.009 --> 11:50.477
OH, GOD. ARE YOU IN DANGER
EMOTIONALLY OR PHYSICALLY?

11:50.510 --> 11:52.946
WELL...KIND OF.

11:52.979 --> 11:54.547
[ GROANS ]
WE WILL TALK ABOUT THIS

11:54.581 --> 11:55.982
AT YOUR SCHEDULED
APPOINTMENT.

11:56.016 --> 11:56.750
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING.

11:56.783 --> 11:58.418
THE FANS ARE TURNING
AGAINST ME,

11:58.451 --> 12:00.020
THE PAPERS
ARE TURNING AGAINST ME.

12:00.053 --> 12:02.022
I MEAN, WHAT THE HELL IS
SO GREAT ABOUT SHANE GIVENS?!

12:02.055 --> 12:04.991
T.K., I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF
MY SON'S TEEN PIZZA PARTY.

12:05.025 --> 12:06.359
I LOVE PEPPERONI.

12:06.393 --> 12:07.761
YOU ARE MY PATIENT.

12:08.828 --> 12:10.797
IF I JUSLET YOU WALTZ IN HERE
ANYTIME OF ANY DAY,

12:13.099 --> 12:15.368
OKAY, SO, WHAT, SO THIS WHOLE
THING IS LIKE A LESSON?

12:17.003 --> 12:18.905
I'M IN DISTRESS, DOC!

12:18.938 --> 12:22.142
WE WILL TALK ABOUT THIS
AT YOUR APPOINTMENT.
NO.

12:22.175 --> 12:24.778
WE WON'T.

12:27.881 --> 12:29.783
[ SIGHS ]

12:31.451 --> 12:32.986
[ GASPS,
EXHALES SHARPLY ]

12:41.428 --> 12:43.930
DO WE, UH,
REALLY HAVE TO DO THIS?

12:43.963 --> 12:47.167
IF WE WANT TO UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU STEAL,

12:47.200 --> 12:51.037
WHAT TRIGGERS
THE SHOPLIFTING -- YES.

12:51.071 --> 12:52.138
WHEN YOU'RE READY,

12:53.106 --> 12:54.240
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAKE OFF
THE SUNGLASSES.

12:54.274 --> 12:55.842
[ GROANS ]

12:55.875 --> 12:58.545
I FEEL LIKE I'M BACK
ON THE RUNWAY

12:58.578 --> 13:00.847
IN MY BIKINI,
WITHOUT A TOP.

13:00.880 --> 13:04.517
OKAY. SO...

13:04.551 --> 13:07.520
DO YOU FEEL ANY URGE?

13:07.554 --> 13:10.857
WHAT, TO STEAL A BELT?
NO.

13:10.890 --> 13:12.992
BUT THERE<i>ARE</i>THINGS
THAT I WANT.

13:13.026 --> 13:14.994
ALL RIGHT. TELL ME.

13:15.028 --> 13:17.130
WELL, THAT NECKLACE?
I LOVE IT.

13:17.163 --> 13:18.565
GOOD.
ALL RIGHT, TAKE IT.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.869
DON'T STEAL IT.
JUST PICK IT UP.

13:22.902 --> 13:24.437
OKAY.

13:32.045 --> 13:33.113
HOW DOES THAT FEEL?

13:33.146 --> 13:35.515
HOT --
OH, HOT IN MY HANDS.

13:35.548 --> 13:37.183
OKAY.
KEEP TELLING ME.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.085
THIS PURSE.

13:39.119 --> 13:40.954
I...I WANT THIS PURSE.

13:40.987 --> 13:42.088
WHY?

13:42.122 --> 13:43.189
I-I DON'T KNOW.
I JUST DO.

13:43.223 --> 13:45.191
WHAT ELSE?

13:45.225 --> 13:46.960
[ SIGHS ]

13:46.993 --> 13:49.629
UH, THAT TOP.
THE GOLD ONE.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.664
AND THOSE JEANS.

13:51.698 --> 13:56.302
UH, THAT JACKET,
WITH THE ZIPPERS.

13:56.336 --> 13:59.172
AND THOSE BOOTS.
DEFINITELY THOSE BOOTS.

13:59.205 --> 14:00.674
OKAY.
NOW WHAT WE ARE GONNA DO

14:00.707 --> 14:02.909
IS WE ARE GOING TO BUY
ALL THESE THINGS

14:02.942 --> 14:04.144
AND SEE WHAT
THAT FEELS LIKE.

14:04.177 --> 14:06.913
BUT I DON'T WANT TO BUY THEM.
I WANT TO<i>TAKE</i>THEM.

14:06.946 --> 14:08.581
THINGS THAT DON'T
BELONG TO ME --

14:08.615 --> 14:11.284
THAT'S WHAT I WANT,
TO TAKE WHAT'S NOT MINE.

14:11.317 --> 14:13.253
OKAY, BUT, SHANNON,
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DO THAT.

14:13.286 --> 14:14.654
YOU'RE GONNA BREATHE.

14:14.688 --> 14:18.058
YOU'RE GONNA EXPERIENCE
THAT SENSATION

14:18.091 --> 14:20.193
<i>WITHOUT</i>GIVING IN TO IT.

14:20.226 --> 14:21.928
ARE YOU BREATHING?

14:21.961 --> 14:23.163
YES.

14:23.196 --> 14:25.165
ALL RIGHT.
'CAUSE IF YOU CAN DO THAT,

14:25.198 --> 14:27.701
THEN YOU CAN STOP
YOURSELF.

14:27.734 --> 14:29.569
I CAN STOP.

14:29.602 --> 14:31.571
YES.

14:31.604 --> 14:33.573
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

14:33.606 --> 14:34.674
LIKE WE SHOULD GO.
OH.

14:39.245 --> 14:41.181
SHANNON, DON'T! WAIT!

14:41.214 --> 14:42.215
[ ALARM BLARES ]
WHAT?!

14:42.248 --> 14:45.051
[ SIGHS ]
THE NECKLACE.

14:45.085 --> 14:47.020
YOU TOOK THE NECKLACE.

14:47.053 --> 14:49.556
[ ALARM CONTINUES ]

14:49.589 --> 14:51.658
WHAT IS WRONG WITH ME?

14:56.262 --> 14:58.365
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

14:58.398 --> 15:00.300
Purnell: SHANNON PRITCHETT IS
SUCKING UP LOOSE JEWELRY

15:00.333 --> 15:01.634
FASTER THAN A HOOVER!

15:01.668 --> 15:03.603
T.K. AND SHANE GOT INTO IT
THIS MORNING.

15:03.636 --> 15:04.971
HELL, WE DON'T NEED TO WORRY

15:05.005 --> 15:06.606
ABOUT PITTSBURGH BEATING US UP
NEXT WEEK.

15:06.639 --> 15:08.141
WE'RE DOING IT TO OURSELVES!

15:08.174 --> 15:10.243
WHAT THE HELL ARE WE DOING
ABOUT ALL THIS?

15:10.276 --> 15:11.745
WELL,
SHANNON'S REMORSEFUL.

15:11.778 --> 15:13.680
SHE'S ALREADY
IN COUNSELING.

15:13.713 --> 15:15.181
AND AS FAR AS T.K.
IS CONCERNED --

15:15.215 --> 15:16.049
HE'S A LOOSE CANNON.

15:17.150 --> 15:20.053
OH, WELL,
HE'S WORKING ON HIS ISSUES.

15:20.086 --> 15:24.124
BUT THAT REQUIRES THAT HE FOCUS
ON THE RIGHT THINGS.

15:24.157 --> 15:25.725
MEANING?

15:25.759 --> 15:29.362
THIS PUBLICITY JUGGERNAUT
IS NOT IN HIS BEST INTEREST.

15:29.396 --> 15:30.730
IT'S A LOT OF PRESSURE.

15:30.764 --> 15:32.365
UH, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

15:32.399 --> 15:35.769
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT TALK-SHOW
APPEARANCES AND ENDORSEMENTS,

15:35.802 --> 15:38.104
NOT STINTS ON "SURVIVOR."

15:38.138 --> 15:40.674
LOOK, I DON'T CARE IF YOU FIX IT
WITH GORILLA GLUE.

15:40.707 --> 15:42.409
I WANT IT FIXED
BY NEXT WEEK'S GAME.

15:42.442 --> 15:44.277
THE LADIES, TOO.

15:44.310 --> 15:46.746
WHEN MARSHALL PITTMAN CALLS ME
FOR THE 14th TIME THIS WEEK,

15:46.780 --> 15:51.084
I'D LIKE TO BE ABLE TO GIVE HIM
SOME<i>GOOD</i>NEWS!

15:51.117 --> 15:53.720
LOOK -- WE ALL WANT
THE SAME THINGS HERE. RIGHT?

15:55.355 --> 15:57.357
[ Laughing ]
CAN'T WE ALL JUST GET ALONG?

15:57.390 --> 16:00.160
THANK YOU, MR. SWITZERLAND.

16:05.665 --> 16:06.700
QUESTION.

16:06.733 --> 16:08.101
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

16:08.134 --> 16:10.770
I HAVE A FRIEND.
HAS A PROBLEM.

16:10.804 --> 16:12.305
ALCOHOL...

16:12.339 --> 16:15.141
MEN. A WHOLE LOT OF...
TROUBLE.

16:15.175 --> 16:17.777
I KEEP BAILING HER OUT.
NOTHING CHANGES.

16:19.779 --> 16:23.783
WELL, IF THERE ARE NO
CONSEQUENCES FOR HER BEHAVIOR,

16:23.817 --> 16:26.686
THEN SHE HAS NO REASON
TO CHANGE.

16:26.720 --> 16:28.421
ENABLING DOESN'T HELP.

16:30.357 --> 16:33.259
NO. IT DOESN'T.

16:33.293 --> 16:35.695
THANKS.

16:58.284 --> 16:59.285
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:59.319 --> 17:00.553
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:00.587 --> 17:02.822
HEY. COME ON IN.
HELLO.

17:05.158 --> 17:06.559
[ SIGHS ]

17:06.593 --> 17:08.461
WHAT -- WHAT'S THAT?

17:08.495 --> 17:11.464
I WENT AND BOUGHT THE CLOTHES
FROM THE BOUTIQUE

17:11.498 --> 17:13.099
THAT YOU WANTED
THE OTHER DAY.

17:13.133 --> 17:14.768
I-I REALLY DON'T
WANT TO TALK ABOUT --

17:14.801 --> 17:16.069
I KNOW.

17:17.103 --> 17:17.837
I JUST THOUGHT THAT WE COULD
LOOK AT THEM TOGETHER.

17:17.871 --> 17:18.838
OKAY?

17:24.244 --> 17:25.845
[ SIGHS ]

17:40.326 --> 17:43.897
OKAY.

17:43.930 --> 17:47.334
OKAY.
WHAT DO YOU SEE?

17:47.367 --> 17:49.135
ABOUT $2,000.

17:49.169 --> 17:51.771
PRINTED SHIRT.

17:51.805 --> 17:52.839
JACKET.

17:52.872 --> 17:55.542
I-I DON'T GET IT.
I --

17:55.575 --> 17:57.277
NECKLACE.

17:57.310 --> 17:59.479
DOES THAT REMIND YOU
OF ANYONE?

17:59.512 --> 18:01.881
NO.

18:04.250 --> 18:09.389
ANYONE YOU KNOW THAT MIGHT OWN
A NECKLACE LIKE THIS?

18:12.258 --> 18:15.395
LEANNE.

18:18.531 --> 18:20.834
I'M TAKING
LEANNE'S THINGS?

18:20.867 --> 18:21.801
WHY?

18:23.937 --> 18:26.239
WELL, I DON'T KNOW!
HOW WOULD<i>I</i>KNOW?!

18:26.272 --> 18:29.809
LOOK, LEANNE AND I
WERE VERY CLOSE

18:29.843 --> 18:31.644
WHEN SHE FIRST
JOINED THE TEAM.

18:31.678 --> 18:32.912
I-I MADE A POINT
OF REACHING OUT TO HER

18:32.946 --> 18:34.381
WHEN HER HUSBAND
WAS DRAFTED,

18:34.414 --> 18:36.383
WELCOMED HER
INTO MY HOME.

18:36.416 --> 18:38.918
AND THEN ONE DAY,
SHE JUST...

18:38.952 --> 18:40.520
STOPPED TALKING TO ME.

18:40.553 --> 18:42.422
AND HOW LONG AGO
WAS THAT?

18:42.455 --> 18:43.823
I DON'T KNOW, EXACTLY.

18:44.924 --> 18:46.626
I THINK IT WAS AROUND THE TIME
OF THE SAN DIEGO ROAD TRIP.

18:46.659 --> 18:48.661
AND DID YOU ASK HER
ABOUT IT?

18:48.695 --> 18:52.365
OH, I TRIED, BUT...

18:52.399 --> 18:53.633
[ SIGHS ]

18:53.667 --> 18:57.404
I SWEAR, DR. SANTINO,

18:57.437 --> 19:01.441
BEFORE THE BRACELET,
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING TO HER.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.411
[ SIGHS ]

19:04.444 --> 19:06.413
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

19:06.446 --> 19:07.313
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

19:10.617 --> 19:12.218
Dani: MY KEYS, MARGO.
I LOSTY KEYS.

19:12.252 --> 19:14.354
I'VE BEEN RUSHING AROUND
SO MUCH,

19:14.387 --> 19:16.489
I MUST HAVE
LEFT THEM SOMEWHERE.

19:16.523 --> 19:18.291
YES, I CALLED A CAB,

19:18.324 --> 19:19.693
BUT TELL HIM I'M GONNA BE THERE
AS SOON AS I CAN

19:19.726 --> 19:22.395
AND THAT I'M SORRY
AND THAT I LOVE HIM.

19:22.429 --> 19:24.564
OKAY. BYE.

19:24.597 --> 19:26.566
Psst! Psst!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING BACK HERE?

19:26.599 --> 19:28.268
COACH CALLED ME IN,

19:28.301 --> 19:29.869
AND NOW I'M PROBABLY GONNA MISS
RAY JAY'S GAME,

19:29.903 --> 19:32.238
AND THEN I'M GONNA GET
HEAD CANCER AGAIN.

19:32.272 --> 19:34.441
BECAUSE I LOST MY KEYS AND
I HAVE TO CALL A FRIGGIN' CAB.

19:34.474 --> 19:36.576
WELL, I'M TAKING OFF RIGHT NOW.
I CAN GIVE YOU A RIDE.

19:36.609 --> 19:38.478
COME ON. CHOP-CHOP.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.447
LET'S GO.
"CHOP-CHOP"?

19:42.482 --> 19:44.384
Irv:<i>HELLO, SPORTS FANS.</i>

19:44.417 --> 19:46.486
<i>THIS IS IRV SUPERFON.</i>

19:46.519 --> 19:48.621
<i>BEFORE WE MOVE ON</i>
<i>TO THE ROUND-TABLE DISCUSSION,</i>

19:48.655 --> 19:51.324
<i>STILL GETTING CALLS ABOUT</i>
<i>T.K.'s MELTDOWN THE OTHER DAY.</i>

19:51.358 --> 19:52.892
KISS MY ASS, IRV.

19:52.926 --> 19:54.928
<i>THE HAWKS HAVE GOT TO</i>
<i>SERIOUSLY THINK</i>

19:54.961 --> 19:57.630
<i>ABOUT HOPPING OFF THE</i>
<i>T.K. TRAIN BEFORE IT DERAILS</i>

19:57.664 --> 20:00.500
<i>INTO A FIREBALL</i>
<i>AND TAKES THE TEAM WITH IT.</i>

20:00.533 --> 20:02.302
OH, YOU JUST GONNA USE MY OWN
METAPHOR AGAINST ME, DAWG?!

20:02.335 --> 20:03.536
[ GRUNTS ]

20:03.570 --> 20:06.373
[ CHEERLEADERS CHANTING ]

20:06.406 --> 20:07.474
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

20:11.544 --> 20:13.313
YOU REALLY DIDN'T
HAVE TO DO THIS. THANK YOU.

20:13.346 --> 20:15.048
I WASN'T GONNA
LEAVE YOU STRANDED.

20:15.081 --> 20:17.751
YOU SURE THAT YOU WANT TO STAY
AND SEE THE GAME?

20:17.784 --> 20:19.552
OH, COME ON,
IT'S PEP BANDS

20:19.586 --> 20:21.321
AND DADS COACHING
FROM THE STANDS.

20:21.354 --> 20:23.590
MARGO? LINDSAY?

20:23.623 --> 20:25.358
IS THAT RAY JAY?

20:25.392 --> 20:26.593
RAY JAY!

20:26.626 --> 20:28.628
OH, MY GOD.

20:34.668 --> 20:35.902
ARE YOU SURE
THAT WE SHOULDN'T HAVE

20:35.935 --> 20:38.405
JUST TAKEN HIM
TO THE HOSPITAL?

20:38.438 --> 20:40.306
DR. FELTON'S
OUR TEAM DOCTOR.

20:40.340 --> 20:41.307
YOU KNOW...

20:41.908 --> 20:42.842
HE WORKS ON
THE $5 MILLION KNEES.

20:43.643 --> 20:44.844
Dr. Felton: MATT.
OH, HEY, JIM.

20:44.878 --> 20:46.079
DR. SANTINO?

20:46.112 --> 20:48.782
YES, YES.
THANK YOU FOR SEEING US.

20:48.815 --> 20:50.083
OH, NO PROBLEM. ANYTHING FOR
A MEMBER OF THE TEAM.

20:50.116 --> 20:53.386
OKAY, SO, YOUR SON HAS
SOME LAXITY IN THE JOINT

20:53.420 --> 20:55.588
AND PROBABLY DAMAGE
TO HIS ACL.

20:55.622 --> 20:56.956
OH,
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

20:56.990 --> 20:59.059
VERY COMMON SPORTS INJURY.

20:59.092 --> 21:01.327
WE'VE SENT HIM FOR AN MRI
TO CONFIRM THE DIAGNOSIS

21:01.361 --> 21:02.929
AND DETERMINE THE EXTENT
OF THE DAMAGE.

21:02.962 --> 21:04.431
RUN THEM ALL.
HAWKS WILL COVER IT.

21:04.464 --> 21:05.965
OH, MY GOD.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

21:05.999 --> 21:07.934
AGAIN, PART OF THE TEAM.

21:07.967 --> 21:09.969
I'LL KEEP YOU UPDATED.

21:10.003 --> 21:11.705
THANK YOU.
APPRECIATE IT.

21:11.738 --> 21:12.706
NICE MEETING YOU.

21:12.739 --> 21:14.074
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:14.107 --> 21:15.709
HEY.
HI.

21:15.742 --> 21:17.410
I'VE GOT YOUR, UH,
HOME MOVIE.

21:17.444 --> 21:19.646
OH, THANK YOSO MUCH.

21:19.679 --> 21:22.015
I'M SORRY.
I'LL NEVER BE THAT STUPID AGAIN.

21:22.048 --> 21:23.116
I'M JUST GONNA MAKE SURE
THE GUY DIDN'T,

21:23.149 --> 21:24.751
YOU KNOW,
PULL A FAST ONE ON ME.

21:24.784 --> 21:26.019
NO, LOOK, PLEASE.
PLEASE, DON'T.

21:26.052 --> 21:27.954
IT'S REALLY EMBARRASSING.
WHY? WHY? EXCUSE ME.

21:30.724 --> 21:32.726
BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT IN IT.

21:32.759 --> 21:35.695
[ SCOFFS ]
KURT WAS GONNA --
NO, YOU LIED TO ME.

21:35.729 --> 21:37.997
I PUT MY JOB AND MY RELATIONSHIP
WITH YOUR DAD

21:38.031 --> 21:39.632
ON THE LINE FOR YOU,

21:39.666 --> 21:40.900
NOT FOR YOUR BOYFRIEND
WHO'S PASSED OUT IN THE TUB.

21:42.068 --> 21:43.903
I'M SORRY. I'M SO SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT ELSE TO DO.

21:43.937 --> 21:45.872
I LOVE HIM.

21:45.905 --> 21:50.744
YOU ARE THROWING YOURSELF AWAY
ON THE WRONG GUYS.

21:50.777 --> 21:52.746
YOU DRINK TOO MUCH.
YOU -- YOU --

21:52.779 --> 21:54.848
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM
BEING ALONE.

21:54.881 --> 21:57.117
REALLY?

21:57.150 --> 21:59.753
IS IT ALL THAT GREAT
HAVING NO ONE?

21:59.786 --> 22:01.388
YOU TELL ME, NICO.

22:04.691 --> 22:08.428
YOU DON'T CARE ENOUGH
ABOUT YOURSELF TO STOP.

22:08.461 --> 22:11.398
AND I CARE TOO MUCH
TO KEEP PICKING UP THE PHONE.

22:17.937 --> 22:21.408
[ DOOR OPENS, SLAMS ]

22:21.441 --> 22:25.745
THANK YOU, MARGO,
FOR BRINGING LINDSAY HOME.

22:25.779 --> 22:27.981
YES, I WILL CALL YOU
IF I FIND OUT ANYTHING NEW.

22:28.014 --> 22:30.717
MM-HMM. YEAH.

22:30.750 --> 22:32.719
[ SIGHS ]

22:36.089 --> 22:38.758
YOU OKAY?

22:38.792 --> 22:41.928
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN
WITH RAY JAY.

22:41.961 --> 22:43.997
WELL, WHAT COULD YOU
HAVE DONE?

22:44.030 --> 22:45.832
HE WOULD HAVE
STILL GOT HURT.

22:47.901 --> 22:50.070
YOU CAN'T BE ERYWHERE.

22:50.103 --> 22:51.538
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:51.571 --> 22:54.808
BELIEVE ME,
I'M FINDING THAT OUT.

22:56.242 --> 22:58.878
HOW'S IT GOING
WITH THE WAGS?

22:58.912 --> 23:02.982
OH, IT'S...GOING.

23:05.218 --> 23:07.220
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT SAN DIEGO?

23:07.253 --> 23:10.223
CITY IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA,
GREAT ZOO. UH...

23:10.256 --> 23:11.558
HA HA.

23:11.591 --> 23:13.827
NO,
IT'S JUST THAT, UH,

23:13.860 --> 23:15.562
SHANNON PRITCHETT
SAID SOMETHING --

23:15.595 --> 23:19.232
SHE MADE A POINT
OF MENTIONING...

23:19.265 --> 23:22.035
DID ANYTHING UNUSUAL HAPPEN
IN SAN DIEGO

23:22.068 --> 23:23.837
ON THIS LAST ROAD TRIP?

23:23.870 --> 23:25.538
BESIDES US WINNING?

23:25.572 --> 23:27.240
UH...

23:27.273 --> 23:30.844
NO, IT WAS JUST LIKE
ANY OTHER ROAD TRIP.

23:30.877 --> 23:31.778
MEANING?

23:33.513 --> 23:36.816
WHAT HAPPENS ON THE ROAD
STAYS ON THE ROAD.

23:36.850 --> 23:37.984
[ LAUGHS ]

23:38.018 --> 23:40.453
WHAT, OMERTÃ ,
LIKE THE MAFIA?

23:42.589 --> 23:44.924
LOOK...

23:44.958 --> 23:45.892
IT'S STRESSFUL.

23:45.925 --> 23:47.794
GUYS ARE AWAY FROM HOME.

23:47.827 --> 23:50.163
THEY GO OUT AT NIGHT,
BURN OFF STEAM.

23:50.196 --> 23:52.565
AND OBVIOUSLY,
THERE ARE WOMEN --

23:52.599 --> 23:55.168
THROWING THEMSELVES
AT ALL THE PLAYERS.

23:55.201 --> 23:57.871
SOME GUYS HANDLE IT WELL.
OTHERS...

23:57.904 --> 23:59.873
AH.

23:59.906 --> 24:00.907
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

24:02.308 --> 24:04.210
WHOA.

24:04.244 --> 24:06.212
FIVE TEXTS IN A ROW.

24:06.246 --> 24:08.148
LET ME GUESS -- T.K.

24:10.784 --> 24:11.951
UH-OH.

24:11.985 --> 24:13.520
I BETTER CALL HIM BACK.

24:13.553 --> 24:15.522
HEY, YO, DR. D,
WHERE IS THE LOVE?

24:15.555 --> 24:17.557
I BEEN TEXTING
AND CALLING YOU ALL DAY.

24:17.590 --> 24:18.925
YEAH, MY SESSION.
I GOT IT.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.527
BUT I CAN'T WAIT
TILL MY SESSION,

24:20.560 --> 24:23.897
'CAUSE IRV SUPERFON IS TRYING
TO DERAIL MY LOCOMOTIVE!

24:23.930 --> 24:25.632
WHY THE HELL NOT?!

24:25.665 --> 24:28.968
W-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
RAY JAY GOT WHAT?

24:29.002 --> 24:31.071
Dr. Felton:
ACETAMINOPHEN AND CODEINE

24:31.104 --> 24:32.939
FOR SHORT-TERM PAIN RELIEF.

24:32.972 --> 24:36.042
HAPPILY IT'S NOT A TEAR.
IT'S JUST A SPRAIN.

24:36.076 --> 24:38.078
SO THE GOOD NEWS IS,
RAY JAY,

24:38.111 --> 24:39.879
FOUR TO SIX WEEKS --
GOOD AS NEW.

24:39.913 --> 24:41.181
FOUR TO SIX WEEKS?

24:41.214 --> 24:43.016
HEY, BEATS SURGERY
AND FOUR TO SIX<i>MONTHS.</i>

24:44.217 --> 24:46.286
YOU, UH, HAVE A VISITOR.

24:47.354 --> 24:49.923
WHOO!
HOW'S IT GOING, BOY?!

24:49.956 --> 24:51.991
T.K.?

24:52.025 --> 24:53.093
WHAT'S UP, MAN?

24:54.094 --> 24:55.095
HEY, I HOPE YOU SMACKED THE HELL
OUT THAT DUDE.

24:56.062 --> 24:57.097
NO, BUT I WILL NEXT TIME
I SEE HIM, FOR SURE.

24:57.130 --> 24:59.966
YOU OKAYED THIS?

25:00.000 --> 25:02.268
NO, I DID NOT.

25:02.302 --> 25:05.605
UM, COME HERE.
OKAY, JUST HEAR ME OUT. I SEE.

25:05.638 --> 25:07.007
YOU LOOK SHADY.
YOU LOOK SHADY TO ME.

25:07.040 --> 25:08.274
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

25:10.043 --> 25:11.077
LEANNE.

25:11.111 --> 25:12.345
HELLO, DR. SANTINO.

25:12.379 --> 25:13.947
THANKS FOR TAKING MY CALL.
COME ON IN.

25:13.980 --> 25:16.116
THANKS.

25:16.149 --> 25:19.185
TELL ME ABOUT SAN DIEGO.

25:26.326 --> 25:28.228
I CAN'T.

25:28.261 --> 25:30.897
THOSE ARE THE RULES. I CAN'T
TALK ABOUT IT WITH ANYONE.

25:30.930 --> 25:34.000
LEANNE, HEY.

25:34.034 --> 25:35.669
YOU CAN TALK ABOUT IT
WITH ME.

25:40.407 --> 25:42.208
[ SIGHS ]

25:42.242 --> 25:43.677
OKAY. UM...

25:46.312 --> 25:49.916
SAN DIEGO,
I SURPRISED DEREK ON THE ROAD.

25:49.949 --> 25:53.186
AND...

25:53.219 --> 25:55.922
I SAW SHANNON'S HUSBAND.

25:55.955 --> 25:57.624
RYAN.

25:57.657 --> 26:00.060
RYAN.

26:00.093 --> 26:04.297
LEAVING HIS HOTEL ROOM
WITH SOMEONE ELSE --

26:04.330 --> 26:06.933
ANOTHER WOMAN.

26:06.966 --> 26:09.002
UH,
RYAN CORNERED ME LATER,

26:09.035 --> 26:11.004
AND HE LET ME KNOW THAT
THERE WOULD BE CONSEQUENCES

26:11.037 --> 26:12.272
FOR MY HUSBAND

26:12.305 --> 26:16.343
IF I TOLD ANYONE,
ESPECIALLY SHANNON.

26:16.376 --> 26:19.245
[ SIGHS ]
SO...

26:19.279 --> 26:23.116
YOU CREATED THIS RIFT
WITH SHANNON

26:23.149 --> 26:25.318
SO THAT YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE TO FACE EACH OTHER.

26:25.352 --> 26:29.089
I TRIED TO TALK TO DEREK
ABOUT IT.

26:29.122 --> 26:34.427
HE TOLD ME,
"YOU DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING."

26:34.461 --> 26:37.764
JUST...

26:37.797 --> 26:39.366
[ SNIFFLES ]

26:39.399 --> 26:43.403
I THOUGHT I MARRIED A MAN,
NOT A FOOTBALL TEAM.

26:45.205 --> 26:47.407
LISTEN...

26:47.440 --> 26:51.711
I CAN'T PRETEND
TO KNOW WHAT IT FEELS LIKE,

26:51.745 --> 26:55.949
THIS ROAD CODE
THAT YOU'RE EXPECTED TO KEEP.

26:55.982 --> 26:59.252
BUT, LEANNE...

26:59.285 --> 27:02.188
NO ONE CAN DICTATE
THE RULES

27:02.222 --> 27:07.060
OF YOUR RELATIONSHIPS...

27:07.093 --> 27:09.362
UNLESS YOU LET THEM.

27:13.733 --> 27:17.070
[ INDISTCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:17.103 --> 27:18.772
IF I'D HAVE KNOWN
YOU WERE HERE,

27:18.805 --> 27:20.340
I WOULD HAVE SHOWERED
AND CHANGED.

27:20.373 --> 27:22.142
OH, WELL, IF YOU SHOWERED
AND CHANGED,

27:22.175 --> 27:24.377
I WOULDN'T BE SO HAPPY
TO BE HERE.

27:24.411 --> 27:26.146
HOW'S DANI'S SON?

27:26.179 --> 27:29.382
ACL SPRAIN,
BUT HIS EGO GOT A BIG BOOST.

27:29.416 --> 27:31.718
T.K. MADE
A SURPRISE APPEARANCE.

27:31.751 --> 27:32.719
SPEAKING OF T.K.,

27:32.752 --> 27:36.322
I WAS THINKING MAYBE
HE SHOULD CONSIDER A CHANGE.

27:36.356 --> 27:38.258
IN WHAT, HIS DIET,
BRAND OF UNDERWEAR?

27:38.291 --> 27:41.428
IN, UM, WHO HE'S SEEING --
THERAPY.

27:41.461 --> 27:44.197
THIS GUY COMES
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.

27:44.230 --> 27:47.434
LOOK, T.K.'s BEHAVIOR
HAS BEEN CONSISTENTLY ERRATIC.

27:47.467 --> 27:50.036
ERRATIC BEHAVIOR
IS WHO THE DUDE IS.

27:50.070 --> 27:52.038
THERAPY TAKES TIME.

27:52.072 --> 27:54.374
MM.

27:54.407 --> 27:57.110
WHAT?

27:57.143 --> 27:59.245
THE CONSTANT ANGLING.

27:59.279 --> 28:00.080
YOU HAVE HAD ISSUES
WITH DANI

28:00.113 --> 28:02.115
SINCE THE MOMENT
YOU STEPPED IN HERE.

28:02.148 --> 28:04.084
THAT IS NOT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

28:04.117 --> 28:05.385
THEN WHAT'S IT ABOUT?

28:05.418 --> 28:07.754
I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU DON'T WANT TO BE THE GUY

28:07.787 --> 28:09.289
WHO BRINGS IN
THE WRONG FIX.

28:09.322 --> 28:10.223
BRINGING IN THE RIGHT FIX

28:10.256 --> 28:12.359
COULD MAKE YOU A HERO
IN PITTMAN'S EYES.

28:12.392 --> 28:17.297
DO YOU SEE A BOYFRIEND
OR ANOTHER PROJECT HERE?

28:17.330 --> 28:20.767
I SEE A MAN
WHO HAS THE INTELLECT,

28:20.800 --> 28:22.302
SAVVY, AND SEX APPEAL

28:22.335 --> 28:24.838
TO END UP AS GENERAL MANAGER
SOMEDAY.

28:24.871 --> 28:26.439
IN TIME, HOPEFULLY.
WELL, THERE'S NO TIME
LIKE THE PRESENT.

28:26.473 --> 28:28.074
STOP!

28:28.108 --> 28:30.143
I'M ON MY TIME.

28:30.176 --> 28:33.279
IF YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE A PROBLEM WITH THAT --

28:33.313 --> 28:35.248
[ SCOFFS ]
I GOT TO GO.

28:44.824 --> 28:47.427
HONEY.

28:47.460 --> 28:52.399
WHAT'D I SAY ABOUT PAIN MEDS
ON AN EMPTY STOMACH?

28:52.432 --> 28:54.334
[ Slurring ]
THEY DON'T AFFECT ME, MOM.
REALLY?

28:58.171 --> 29:00.573
UM...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

29:00.607 --> 29:01.508
HONEY...

29:01.541 --> 29:06.579
I KNOW YOU ACT LIKE
IT DOESN'T BOTHER YOU

29:06.613 --> 29:10.316
THAT I'M GONE SO MUCH THESE DAYS
FOR WORK.

29:10.350 --> 29:14.487
MA...
I LOVE YOUR NEW JOB.

29:19.859 --> 29:23.897
YEAH, SO, RAY JAY...

29:23.930 --> 29:26.433
THAT STORY
FROM ENGLISH CLASS,

29:26.466 --> 29:32.138
YOU KNOW, THE MOM DYING
WITH THE BRAIN TUMOR.

29:32.172 --> 29:35.408
[ CHUCKLES ] YOU TOTALLY
DIDN'T WRITE THAT, DID YOU?

29:35.442 --> 29:38.311
NO.

29:38.345 --> 29:41.281
LINDSAY WROTE THAT.
YOU KNOW I SUCK AT WRITING.

29:41.314 --> 29:42.849
YES, I DO.

29:42.882 --> 29:45.352
SHE OWED ME FOR NOT NARCING
ON HER WHEN SHE GOT BUSTED.

29:45.385 --> 29:48.355
RIGHT, BUSTED.

29:48.388 --> 29:50.423
FOR SELLING T.K.'s STUFF
AT THE STADIUM.

29:50.457 --> 29:54.194
T.K. IS THE MAN.

29:54.227 --> 29:55.862
ALWAYS COMES THROUGH
FOR A FRIEND.

29:55.895 --> 29:57.597
DOES HE, NOW?

29:57.630 --> 29:59.599
HE -- HE GOT ME
INTO CLUB ZARA.

29:59.632 --> 30:02.502
HOT CLUB.
HOT LADIES.

30:02.535 --> 30:06.906
AND WHEN MY CAR GOT STOLEN,
HE BOUGHT ME A NEW ONE.

30:06.940 --> 30:09.609
[ MOANS ]

30:09.642 --> 30:10.944
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

30:14.514 --> 30:15.949
AM I IN TROUBLE?

30:24.457 --> 30:28.261
IT'S BAD ENOUGH THAT T.K.
SHOWS UP AT MY HOUSE UNANNOUNCED

30:29.062 --> 30:29.496
WITH THE OCCASIONAL
STRIPPER,

30:30.463 --> 30:31.664
CRASHES MY SON'S PIZZA PARTY
OR THE DOCTOR'S.

30:31.698 --> 30:33.299
BUT W I FIND OUT

30:33.333 --> 30:36.002
THAT HE'S TAKEN MY UNDERAGE SON
TO A CLUB,

30:36.036 --> 30:36.970
BOUGHT HIM A CAR.

30:37.003 --> 30:38.104
HE WHAT?

30:38.138 --> 30:39.639
YEAH.
OHH.

30:39.673 --> 30:42.409
T.K. HASN'T
JUST CROSSED THE LINE,

30:42.442 --> 30:45.545
HE HAS BLOWN
THE FRICKIN' LINE UP!

30:45.578 --> 30:48.648
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU'RE 100% RIGHT.

30:48.682 --> 30:51.418
IT'S JUST...

30:51.451 --> 30:54.421
YOU KNOW THAT T.K.'s
ON TENDER FOOTING RIGHT NOW.

30:54.454 --> 30:55.522
THAT'S ALL
I'M ASKING YOU --

30:55.555 --> 30:57.557
CAN YOU JUST WAIT
UNTIL AFTER THE GAME

30:57.590 --> 30:59.392
TO TALK TO HIM
ABOUT ALL THIS STUFF?

30:59.426 --> 31:00.660
IT'S FOR THE SAKE
OF THE TEAM.

31:00.694 --> 31:02.362
OKAY.

31:02.395 --> 31:04.464
IT'S JUST THAT, I MEAN,
THERE COMES A POINT

31:04.497 --> 31:07.067
WHERE I CAN'T
BE COMPROMISED ANYMORE.

31:07.100 --> 31:11.104
I DO HAVE A THERAPEUTICODE
THAT I NEED TO LIVE BY.

31:11.137 --> 31:12.672
I GET IT.

31:12.706 --> 31:14.507
[ SIGHS ]

31:17.677 --> 31:20.146
SAN DIEGO?
W-WHAT ABOUT IT?

31:20.180 --> 31:21.414
I WASN'T THERE.

31:21.448 --> 31:23.950
TELL ME ABOUT
THE ROAD CODE.

31:23.983 --> 31:26.419
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:26.453 --> 31:28.355
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT IT?

31:29.389 --> 31:32.359
YOU GET USED TO
A CERTAIN LIFESTYLE,

31:32.392 --> 31:35.395
BEING A FOOTBALL WIFE,
DR. SANTINO.

31:35.428 --> 31:39.399
IT'S A TRADE-OFF,
ACCEPTING THE POSSIBILITY

31:39.432 --> 31:43.937
THAT THERE ARE THINGS
IN YOUR HUSBAND'S LIFE THAT...

31:47.507 --> 31:50.577
REMEMBER
WHAT WE TALKED ABOUT

31:50.610 --> 31:55.448
WITH THE SHOPLIFTING BEING
TRIGGERED BY LOSS OR DEPRESSION?

31:55.482 --> 31:57.183
MM.

31:57.217 --> 32:00.153
YOU LOST SOMETHING,
DIDN'T YOU?

32:00.186 --> 32:02.989
A FRIEND.

32:05.058 --> 32:07.627
ALL RIGHT, SO...

32:07.660 --> 32:12.098
I TOOK THINGS THAT REMINDED ME
OF LEANNE. SO WHAT?

32:12.132 --> 32:15.001
YOU'RE SUGGESTING I WANT
SOMETHING THAT SHE HAS?

32:15.035 --> 32:17.070
MY HUSBAND
IS A STAR SAFETY.

32:17.103 --> 32:19.673
HE MAKES 10 TIMES
WHAT HER HUSBAND MAKES.

32:19.706 --> 32:21.675
WE ARE WELL-OFF,
SECURE.

32:21.708 --> 32:23.710
YOU TELL ME --
YOU TELL ME,

32:23.743 --> 32:26.646
WHAT THE HELL DOES SHE HAVE
THAT I DON'T HAVE?

32:26.680 --> 32:28.615
TELL ME.

32:28.648 --> 32:31.418
THE TRUTH.

32:39.659 --> 32:42.595
MAYBE YOU DO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED IN SAN DIEGO.

32:50.804 --> 32:54.040
TELL ME WHAT IT MEANS...

32:54.074 --> 32:56.810
WHEN YOUR HUSBAND
HAS TWO CELLPHONES.

32:56.843 --> 33:02.782
WHEN YOU CAN'T GET AHOLD OF HIM
AT 3:00 A.M. ON THE ROAD.

33:02.816 --> 33:07.654
WHEN 52 OTHER PLAYERS,
THEIR WIVES, AND THE PRESS

33:07.687 --> 33:13.226
ALL KNOW THAT YOUR HUSBAND
IS A DOG.

33:14.828 --> 33:17.097
I GET IT.

33:17.130 --> 33:21.634
I JUST THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE DIFFERENT FOR US.

33:21.668 --> 33:25.105
MAYBE IF I KEPT MY BODY.

33:25.138 --> 33:28.508
IF I WAS JUST...

33:28.541 --> 33:30.443
A REALLY GOOD WIFE.

33:30.477 --> 33:34.514
SHANNON,
YOUR HUSBAND'S CHOICES

33:34.547 --> 33:37.684
HAVE NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU.

33:37.717 --> 33:42.756
I WANT TO WALK AWAY, BUT IT
JUST SCARES THE HELL OUT OF ME.

33:42.789 --> 33:46.593
I GOT TWO KIDS.
THIS IS MY WHOLE LIFE.

33:46.626 --> 33:50.463
I WILL HELP YOU
COME UP WITH A PLA

33:50.497 --> 33:53.700
IF THAT'S
WHAT YOU DECIDE.

33:53.733 --> 33:56.803
AND WE CAN CONTINUE
TO WORK TOGETHER

33:56.836 --> 33:58.638
FOR AS LONG AS YOU LIKE.

34:00.607 --> 34:02.742
OH. [ SIGHS ]

34:02.776 --> 34:04.744
AND LEANNE?

34:06.479 --> 34:09.482
WHAT ABOUT LEANNE?

34:18.558 --> 34:20.326
JULIETTE.

34:20.360 --> 34:23.296
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER
MY CALLS.

34:23.329 --> 34:24.831
YOU CAN'T BE IN HERE.

34:24.864 --> 34:26.633
I HAVE TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

34:26.666 --> 34:28.335
WELL, WE HAVE TO GET YOU
OUT OF COACH'S OFFICE.

34:28.368 --> 34:32.138
I DUMPED KURT.

34:32.172 --> 34:33.807
YOU WERE RIGHT.
HE'S A CREEP.

34:35.642 --> 34:37.577
AND?

34:37.610 --> 34:41.247
I DON'T WANT TO
KEEP MESSING UP.

34:50.757 --> 34:53.526
THEN DON'T.

34:54.794 --> 34:56.930
HELP ME.

34:56.963 --> 34:59.265
FOR REAL.

35:03.770 --> 35:06.906
IF YOU'RE LOOKING FOR T.K.,
HE JUST FINISHED A MASSAGE.

35:06.940 --> 35:09.242
HE SHOULD BE OUT
IN 15 OR 20.

35:09.275 --> 35:11.878
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

35:13.346 --> 35:15.749
I'VE RUN AT THIS PACE
EVER SINCE I WAS 7 YEARS OLD,

35:15.782 --> 35:17.684
TRYING TO POWER MY WAY
THROUGH GIRL SCOUTS.

35:19.686 --> 35:21.554
WELL, I'M SURE YOU LOOKED CUTE
IN THE UNIFORM.

35:21.588 --> 35:23.690
ACTUALLY,
I TRIED REDESIGNING THEM.

35:23.723 --> 35:25.191
OF COURSE YOU DID.
WELL, THEY WERE OUTDATED.

35:25.225 --> 35:26.693
NEEDED REBRANDING.

35:26.726 --> 35:28.695
WELL, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO BRAND ME.

35:28.728 --> 35:30.697
I KNOW.

35:30.730 --> 35:32.365
I CAN BE PUSHY.

35:32.399 --> 35:33.767
NO.
LITTLE AGGRESSIVE?

35:33.800 --> 35:35.635
WHO, YOU?

35:35.669 --> 35:37.604
WELL, IT IS WHAT
MAKES ME SUCCESSFUL.

35:37.637 --> 35:38.738
YES.

35:38.772 --> 35:40.206
BUT...

35:40.240 --> 35:41.841
IT DOESN'T BELONG
IN OUR RELATIONSHIP.

35:41.875 --> 35:43.710
AND I GET THAT.

35:43.743 --> 35:45.712
GOOD.

35:51.351 --> 35:53.653
I'M GONNA MISS YOU
WHEN YOU GO TO SAN FRANCISCO.

35:53.687 --> 35:55.388
GOOD.

35:55.422 --> 35:58.258
I'M BRINGING MY THINGS
BACK WITH ME.

35:58.291 --> 36:01.761
* LOVE BLEEDS INTO STRIFE

36:01.795 --> 36:03.697
VERY GOOD.

36:03.730 --> 36:05.965
* HIDDEN IN PLAIN SIGHT

36:05.999 --> 36:07.834
* IT'S STILL HARD TO SEE

36:07.867 --> 36:09.302
IF YOU WANT ME, I'LL BE
JUST IN THE OFFICE, OKAY?

36:09.336 --> 36:12.405
* OH, THE IRONY IN LIFE

36:12.439 --> 36:13.807
THANKS.

36:15.308 --> 36:17.310
* CUT FROM THE SAME STONE

36:17.344 --> 36:21.614
* WE ALL SHINE A DIFFERENT HUE

36:21.648 --> 36:25.418
* WHY, THEN,
DO WE SHARPEN OUR KNIVES? *

36:27.020 --> 36:27.887
* CUTTING DOWN OTHERS

36:27.921 --> 36:29.622
Dani: HEY, LINDS?

36:29.656 --> 36:32.726
* TO PROTECT
OUR POINTS OF VIEW *

36:32.759 --> 36:36.963
I WANTED TO KNOW IF YOU
WANT TO GO TO A MOVIE TOGETHER.

36:36.996 --> 36:38.331
I'M GOING TO WINTER'S.

36:38.365 --> 36:40.233
OH.

36:42.802 --> 36:45.739
[ SIGHS ]

36:45.772 --> 36:47.841
LINDSAY...

36:47.874 --> 36:48.975
HOW ARE YOU?

36:49.009 --> 36:50.844
I'M FINE.

36:50.877 --> 36:55.982
FINE AS IN GAVE ME A BRAIN TUMOR
AND KILLED ME OFF?

36:56.016 --> 36:57.951
IT WAS JUST A STORY.

36:57.984 --> 37:00.854
OKAY, WELL...

37:00.887 --> 37:03.790
I'M NOT GONNA PRETEND
THAT IT DIDN'T HURT MY FEELINGS.

37:03.823 --> 37:07.360
BUT I KNOW THAT I HAVE BEEN
READ PRETTY THIN LATELY

37:07.394 --> 37:11.364
AND THAT YOU HAVE GOTTEN
THE SHORT END MORE THAN RAY JAY.

37:11.398 --> 37:12.766
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I GET IT.

37:12.799 --> 37:14.901
YOU'RE A SINGLE MOM,
A TEAM OF ONE NOW.

37:14.934 --> 37:15.969
I GET IT.

37:16.002 --> 37:19.406
TEAM OF ONE.

37:23.710 --> 37:24.678
DO YOU WANT TO KNOW

37:24.711 --> 37:27.047
THE THING I NOTICED THE MOST
ABOUT YOUR STORY?

37:27.080 --> 37:31.818
WELL, I MEAN, THE<i>OTHER</i>THING
I NOTICED ABOUT YOUR STORY?

37:33.086 --> 37:34.954
YOU'RE TALENTED.

37:36.823 --> 37:39.325
YOU ARE INCREDIBLY GIFTED.

37:39.359 --> 37:43.463
IRONIC AND IMAGINATIVE.

37:43.496 --> 37:46.433
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN
IT WAS YOUR VOICE.

37:48.134 --> 37:50.804
* HIDDEN IN PLAIN SIGHT

37:50.837 --> 37:53.506
KEEP WRITING.

37:53.540 --> 37:55.909
JUST DON'T KILL ME.

37:55.942 --> 37:58.511
THE IRONY IN LIFE *

38:17.697 --> 38:23.536
COTTON SHEETS?
NO HEATED TOWEL RACKS?

38:23.570 --> 38:26.439
HOW WILL I EVER SURVIVE?
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:26.473 --> 38:29.376
WHAT DOESN'T KILL YOU
MAKES YOU STRONGER.

38:29.409 --> 38:32.946
I'M DOING THIS FOROU,
NOT HIM.

38:32.979 --> 38:36.950
DON'T DO THIS FOR ME
OR YOUR FATHER

38:36.983 --> 38:40.553
OR ANYBODY ELSE.

38:40.587 --> 38:43.023
YOU DO IT FOR YOURSELF,
JULIETTE.

38:43.056 --> 38:45.992
YOU'RE STARTING TO SOUND
LIKE A THERAPIST.

38:46.026 --> 38:47.560
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:51.464 --> 38:53.466
THANK YOU.

38:53.500 --> 38:56.002
DON'T MENTION IT.

38:56.036 --> 38:57.437
TO ANYONE.

39:08.148 --> 39:10.583
IT'S A SHAME
YOU NEVER HAD KIDS.

39:10.617 --> 39:14.654
YOU WOULD HAVE MADE
A GREAT DAD.

39:22.462 --> 39:24.798
T.K.: YO.
[ LAUGHING ]

39:24.831 --> 39:27.100
YOU PICK THAT GAME
YESTERDAY?

39:27.133 --> 39:29.536
KILLED IT!
FANS ATE IT UP.

39:29.569 --> 39:31.137
BACK ON TEAM T.K.

39:31.171 --> 39:32.672
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

39:32.706 --> 39:33.673
YOU SHOULD BE.

39:33.707 --> 39:35.175
AND IRV SUPERFON --

39:35.208 --> 39:38.011
THIS FOOL REALLY THINKS
HE CAN GET ME.

39:38.044 --> 39:41.481
TAKE THAT, BIOTCH.
[ LAUGHS ]

39:41.514 --> 39:45.585
TERRENCE, YOU'VE SAID IT'S
IMPORTANT TO YOU TO BE LIKED.

39:45.618 --> 39:47.754
FAN LOVE FILLS THE SEATS,
DOC.

39:47.787 --> 39:50.457
THAT'S WHY YOU PLAY?
TO FILL THE SEATS?

39:50.490 --> 39:53.460
WHAT YOU GETTING AT?

39:53.493 --> 39:56.596
THERE ARE SOME PLACES
WHERE IT IS HEALTHY

39:56.629 --> 39:59.866
TO SEEK LOVE
AND ADMIRATION.

39:59.899 --> 40:03.636
AND THEN THERE ARE SOME PLACES
WHERE MAYBE IT'S NOT.

40:05.238 --> 40:09.142
RAY JAY HAS TOLD ME ABOUT
THE EXTENT OF YOUR FRIENDSHIP,

40:09.175 --> 40:12.145
ABOUT YOU GUYS HANGING OUT
AT THE CLUB.

40:12.178 --> 40:15.248
NO. OH. IT DID NOT
EVEN GO DOWN LIKE THAT.

40:15.281 --> 40:17.250
THAT YOU
BOUGHT HIM A CAR?

40:17.283 --> 40:18.485
RAY JAY WAS HEMMED UP.

40:19.419 --> 40:20.520
I HELPED HIM OUT OF A SITUATION.
THAT WAS IT.

40:21.521 --> 40:22.455
AND AS FAR AS THE CLUB GOES,
HE JUST SHOWED UP.

40:22.489 --> 40:25.158
DOC, IT'S NOT LIKE
I LET HIM DRINK ANYTHING.

40:25.191 --> 40:26.159
COME ON.

40:26.192 --> 40:27.894
[ LAUGHS ]

40:27.927 --> 40:29.829
YOU'RE MY PATIENT.

40:29.863 --> 40:34.567
YOU CANNOT HAVE A RELATIONSHIP
WITH MY SON

40:34.601 --> 40:37.704
THAT I FIND UNACCEPTABLE.

40:37.737 --> 40:41.675
AND THAT MEANS TEXTING,
CALLING,

40:41.708 --> 40:44.110
SIGNING MERCHANDISE,
BUYING CARS.

40:44.144 --> 40:46.680
YOU'RE PISSED OFF ABOUT THE CLUB
AND THE CAR -- GOT THAT.

40:46.713 --> 40:50.550
I WANT TO KNOW WHY IT IS
THAT YOU FEEL IT'S OKAY

40:50.583 --> 40:54.220
TO BREAK EVERY BOUNDARY
THAT I HAVE SET.

40:54.254 --> 40:59.526
I THINK THAT IT IS IMPORTANT
FOR US TO LOOK AT THAT.

40:59.559 --> 41:01.561
YOU KNOW WHAT, DOC?

41:01.594 --> 41:03.196
DON'T NOBODY CARE
ABOUT YOUR BOUNDARIES.

41:03.229 --> 41:05.265
YOU CAN'T JUST PUT ME
IN A LITTLE BOX

41:05.298 --> 41:08.601
AND EXPECT ME NOT TO MAKE
A MOVE WITHOUT ASKING.

41:08.635 --> 41:10.236
I'M NOT THAT KIND OF DUDE.

